data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","content_index":0,"item_id":"msg_02da7a386b89e7bf0069b1408346908195a692614246942643","logprobs":[],"output_index":1,"sequence_number":433,"text":"TypeScript is an open-source programming language developed by Microsoft that extends JavaScript by adding optional static typing. This enhancement allows developers to catch errors at compile time, leading to more robust and maintainable code. TypeScript is a superset of JavaScript, meaning all valid JavaScript code is also valid TypeScript code. ([typescriptlang.org](https://www.typescriptlang.org/?utm_source=openai))\n\n**Key Features of TypeScript:**\n\n- **Static Typing:** TypeScript introduces static typing to JavaScript, enabling developers to define variable types explicitly. This feature helps in identifying type-related errors during development, reducing runtime issues. ([developer.mozilla.org](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Glossary/TypeScript?utm_source=openai))\n\n- **Type Inference:** Even without explicit type annotations, TypeScript can infer types based on the assigned values, providing flexibility while maintaining type safety.\n\n- **Interfaces and Generics:** TypeScript supports interfaces and generics, allowing for the creation of reusable and flexible code structures.\n\n- **Modern JavaScript Features:** TypeScript supports features from the latest ECMAScript standards, such as async/await, modules, and destructuring, ensuring compatibility with modern JavaScript practices.\n\n**Getting Started with TypeScript:**\n\n1. **Installation:** Install Node.js from the official website. Then, install TypeScript globally using npm:\n\n   ```bash\n   npm install -g typescript\n   ```\n\n2. **Writing TypeScript Code:** Create a `.ts` file and write your TypeScript code. For example:\n\n   ```typescript\n   let message: string = \"Hello, World!\";\n   console.log(message);\n   ```\n\n3. **Compiling TypeScript:** Compile the TypeScript file into JavaScript using the TypeScript compiler:\n\n   ```bash\n   tsc filename.ts\n   ```\n\n4. **Running the Compiled JavaScript:** Execute the generated JavaScript file using Node.js:\n\n   ```bash\n   node filename.js\n   ```\n\nFor a comprehensive guide and documentation, refer to the official TypeScript website. ([typescriptlang.org](https://www.typescriptlang.org/?utm_source=openai))\n\nTo further enhance your understanding, consider watching the following tutorial:\n\n[TypeScript Tutorial For Beginners](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cDeTUYkaEkg&utm_source=openai)\n "}

